title: school athletes of the week
text:
The Dispatch high-school Athletes of the Week, based on performances from Sept. 21 to 27:
Karri Stadulis OLENTANGY LIBERTY, FIELD HOCKEY Stadulis, a senior, scored three goals in a 6-0 win over Dayton Oakwood and two goals in an 8-0 win over Dublin Coffman.
Alicia Donley COLUMBUS SCHOOL FOR GIRLS, SOCCER Donley, a freshman, scored the winning goal as time expired in a 1-0 win over Fairbanks, tallied three goals and an assist in a 5-1 win over Ready and had both goals in a 2-0 win over Wellington.
Stadulis and Donley will receive plaques from Motorists Insurance. Coaches are encouraged to email sports@dispatch.com or fax 614-461-8798 by 4 p.m. Mondays with nominations. 
In addition to the two Athletes of the Week,  The Dispatch  recognizes a top performer in each sport in season:
Brendon White OLENTANGY LIBERTY, FOOTBALL White, a junior defensive back and receiver, had two interceptions, returned a kickoff 91 yards for a touchdown and had a 23-yard touchdown reception in Libertyâ€™s 42-17 victory over unbeaten Upper Arlington.
Micah Miller GRANDVIEW, BOYS SOCCER Miller, a senior goalie, made a rare appearance at forward and scored six goals in an 8-2 win over West Jefferson. He returned to goal and made four saves in a 3-2 win over Fairbanks.
Hunter Moore OLENTANGY ORANGE, BOYS CROSS COUNTRY Moore, a junior, topped a field of 91 runners to win at Pickerington Central in 16 minutes, 01.89 seconds. His 11-second margin of victory helped Orange take the team title with 39 points.
Sydnee Mangette LIBERTY UNION, GIRLS CROSS COUNTRY Mangette, a sophomore, placed first among 141 runners in the Division II section of the Bob Reall Invitational at Lancaster. Her time of 18:59.7 ranks second in central Ohio in the division.
Nick Willis NEWARK CATHOLIC, BOYS GOLF Willis, a junior, shot 1-over-par 73 with three birdies for medalist honors in the Licking County League tournament at Longaberger Golf Club. The Green Wave won by one stroke over Granville. Willis clinched LCL player-of-the-year honors.
Amelia Lee HILLIARD DAVIDSON, GIRLS GOLF Lee, a freshman, shot 79 to place fourth and help the Wildcats win the Marysville Invitational. She also shot 37 in winning a match against Olentangy at Buck Ridge Golf Course.
Erin McCullough DELAWARE CHRISTIAN, VOLLEYBALL McCullough, a senior, had 50 digs, 28 kills and seven assists in leading the team to a 3-0 victory over Granville Christian and 2-0 victories over Columbus Academy and Columbus School for Girls. She was 25 for 26 in service reception.
Kyra Jung UPPER ARLINGTON, GIRLS TENNIS Jung, a junior, defeated Georgia Tuckerman of Columbus Academy 6-1, 6-2 and Sylvia Goldsmith of Lexington 6-0, 6-0. Jung is 8-1 in singles for the Golden Bears.
